         <abstract>
            <p>This paper reports and analyzes the results of a survey of the chief financial officers of a large sample of electric utilities in the U.S. The purpose of the survey was to provide evidence on the parameters these companies use to establish and communicate their goals with respect to their capital structures and also to explore the criteria they consider to be important in choosing these objectives.</p>
